Author:
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: I had a stated interest in the numerous herds of cattle and flocks of sheep which roved in a half-wild state over many miles of the surrounding country, and to which I was about to act as stock-keeper - a kind of colonial head shepherd. .. A stock-keeper may be said to live in his saddle, in a perpetual condition of hunting, assisted by his tailless dogs.
